CoManagedEntity.description: Self-Managed Entities have their own AAS. This is why a reference to this asset is specified as well (Entity/asset). Additionally, further property statements (compare to [15]) can be added to the asset that are not specified in the AAS of the asset itself because they are specified in relation to the complex I4.0 Component only.

SelfManagedEntity.description: For co-managed entities there is no separate AAS. The relationships and property statements of such entities are managed within the AAS of the composite I4.0 Component.
